From b0b8526646c2df51ad0c2339187939f1a8abd924 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Paul Gofman <pgofman@codeweavers.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Dec 2025 18:37:14 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 3/6] fsync: Introduce futex-based inproc sync backend.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Developed by Elizabeth Figura <z.figura12@gmail.com>.
Contains later modifications and workarounds by Paul Gofman.

Also includes patches by:

- André Almeida <andrealmeid@collabora.com> (switch to futex_waitv
  kernel interface, better timeout handling with futex_waitv);
- Derek Lesho <dlesho@codeweavers.com> (type check in some event
  functions);
- Mateusz Piórkowski <mati7337@protonmail.ch> (also consider EPERM
  when checking if futex_waitv is available;
- Rémi Bernon <rbernon@codeweavers.com> (use aligned 64bit types for
  fsync atomics);
- Zhiyi Zhang <zzhang@codeweavers.com> (type check in more event
  functions).

Squashed into a single commit during rebase on top of Wine inproc
sync / ntsync backend. The rebase mostly changed how fsync is plugged
into the Wine cross-process sync objects infrastructure and now
is more of an alternative second backend to 'inproc sync' framework
rather than the full alternative sync primitives implementation.
